The Police Command in Enugu State has arrested one Nnaji who allegedly threatens to kidnap and murder his employer. He was said to have sent the threats via text messages and the internet. The Command’s Public Relations Officer, SP Ebere Amaraizu, who said this in a statement made available to the News Agency of Nigeria on Saturday in Enugu, added that the suspect demanded money from the affected people. Amaraizu said that the suspect was arrested on Friday by operatives from the Central Police Station, Enugu, through intelligence information. READ ALSO: Flood sweeps 11-year-old boy, rescuer to death in Lagos He said that the operatives swung into action after receiving a report from the suspect’s victim, an Enugu-based businessman and employer of the suspect. The police spokesman noted that the complainant had been receiving threats from the suspect who said he would kidnap and murder him if he failed to provide the amount he demanded. “Following the report and intelligence information gathered, the suspect was promptly nabbed for allegedly issuing threats via the internet and text messages to his boss. “The suspect was identified as the personal gardener of the victim (the Enugu-based businessman). “The suspect, following his arrest, revealed how he and some of his cohorts usually disturb their victims with their nefarious activities. “The state Commissioner of Police, Mr Ahmad Abdurrahman, has directed for a full scale investigation into the nefarious activities,’’ he said. According to Amaraizu, the suspect has regretted his actions, attributing it to “an act of Satan.’’ (NAN)